"n.敌对，不友好，憎恨 【英】 n. 敌对状态，敌意(a feeling of enmity) 【例】 His colleagues were hostile to his suggestions. 无 无 hostility (n.)  early 15c., from Middle French hostilité ""enmity"" (15c.), or directly from Late Latin hostilitatem (nominative hostilitas) ""enmity,"" from Latin hostilis, from hostis ""enemy"" (see guest). Hostilities in the sense of ""warfare"" attested from 1610s."
